// Example configuration for integrating tinyMem with Cursor or Claude Desktop
//
// How to use:
// 1. Locate your claude_desktop_config.json file.
//    - macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
//    - Windows: %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json
//    - Linux: ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
//
// 2. Merge the "mcpServers" object from this example into your existing config file.
//
// 3. IMPORTANT: Replace "/path/to/tinymem" with the absolute path to your
//    tinymem executable file. You can find the path by running `which tinymem`
//    (on macOS/Linux) or `where tinymem` (on Windows) in your terminal.
//
// 4. Restart Cursor / Claude Desktop.

{
  "mcpServers": {
    "tinymem": {
      "command": "/path/to/tinymem",
      "args": [
        "mcp"
      ],
      "env": {}
    }
  }
}
